# Contentful Safety Rules

## Ask Before Assuming

- If a Contentful API call returns **404 / NotFound** for an entry or asset, **stop and ask the user** whether they deleted it or if something else is wrong. Do NOT silently skip, retry with --force, or attempt cleanup on your own.
- Never assume orphaned content exists in the target space — the user may have already cleaned it up manually.

## Surgical Retries

- When a migration partially fails (e.g. entries created but assets failed), **only retry the failed step** — do not re-run the entire migration with --force.
- If only an asset failed, retry only the asset creation. If only linking failed, retry only linking. Do not create duplicate entries.

## Destructive Operations

- Never delete entries or assets in the target space without explicit user confirmation.
- Never run --force unless the user explicitly asks for it — prefer the default dedup/remap behavior.
